 will be shared.&nbsp; <b>PPT on Revised Shillong Airport elevations held on 04.07.2025. Below are the action points: A bilateral meeting between AAI &amp; SG of Meghalaya was held and update will be provided by 18.08.2025. Meeting between Secretary (Transport) and AAI to be held after 25.08.2025&nbsp;</b></font>','2025-08-25 00:00:00.000000',3,'lower-roman',0,14,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.783770','2025-10-29 01:54:34.917652',2),(710,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Incorporate local themes (eg. Living Root Bridges) in airport design.</font>',NULL,4,'bullet',0,15,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.787704','2025-08-18 10:15:05.787704',NULL),(711,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Use caves and monoliths (e.g., Mawmluh cave) as design inspiration.</font>',NULL,4,'bullet',0,16,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.791107','2025-08-18 10:15:05.791107',NULL),(712,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Prefer traditional Khasi styles over rigid geometric structures.</font>',NULL,4,'bullet',0,17,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.794935','2025-08-18 10:15:05.794935',NULL),(713,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">State to <b>nominate a senior officer</b> for daily project monitoring and coordination with Air India.&nbsp;</font>',NULL,3,'lower-roman',1,18,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.803310','2025-08-18 10:15:05.803310',NULL),(714,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Work on <b>MoEF-related clearances and state-level clearances</b> on daily basis to reduce project timelines in favor of State (done)</font>',NULL,3,'lower-roman',0,19,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.807922','2025-08-18 10:15:05.807922',NULL),(715,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Follow up on Action Items during Visit to <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Sikkim</span></b></font>',NULL,1,'decimal',0,20,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.812537','2025-08-18 10:15:05.812537',NULL),(716,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>13 delayed projects funded by MDoNER</b> - Documents reconciliation and Project - <b>Next Update on % Progress by - <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">31/10</span></b></font>','2025-10-31 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,21,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.816679','2025-08-18 10:15:05.816679',NULL),(717,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">No. of Projects to be completed by 31/12/25: 01 nos.- <b>Phy. Progress- 96.67% </b>(as on 30.06.25) -&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"><b>31/12</b></span></font>','2025-12-31 00:00:00.000000',3,'lower-roman',0,22,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.820241','2025-08-18 10:15:05.820241',NULL),(718,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">No. of Projects to be completed by 31/03/26: 01 nos. - <b>Phy. Progress- 17%.</b> (as on 30.06.25)- <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"><b>31/03</b></span></font>','2026-03-31 00:00:00.000000',3,'lower-roman',0,23,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.823673','2025-08-18 10:15:05.823673',NULL),(719,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">No. of Projects at a halt: 01 nos. <b>Phy. Progress- 72%. </b>(as on 30.06.25) Work stopped after damage to bridge &amp; road formation connecting to the work site by flooding of Teesta Basin on 7th October 2024. <b>Revised proposal amounting to Rs.1198.98 lakh submitted for sanction to the Ministry. - <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">31/03</span></b></font>',NULL,3,'lower-roman',0,24,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.827193','2025-08-18 10:15:05.827193',NULL),(720,26,NULL,'<font color=\"#00b050\" face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" size=\"2\">No. of Projects physically completed:10 nos. (Done)</font>',NULL,3,'lower-roman',0,25,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.831121','2025-08-18 10:15:05.831121',NULL),(721,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Submission of a proposal for revival and marketing of Tawang’s non-wood handmade paper</b> -Proposal Prepared and submitted to MDoNER for an amount of Rs 20 crore for consideration under the schemes of MDoNER. State Government will first set up a unit at an estimated cost of Rs. 4.95 cr. DPR has been uploaded on PVS portal and project considered in SEC meeting and <b>AFS has been issued on 21.07.2025. The Implementing Agency for Tawang’s non-wood handmade paper project is the Department of Textile and Handloom, Government of Arunachal Pradesh. The work has already been started. Tender has been floated on 04.08.2025. Progress to be monitored&nbsp;</b></font>','2025-08-25 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,26,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.835290','2025-08-18 10:15:05.835290',NULL),(722,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Implementation of <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">USOF projects </span>to improve tele density</b>- Schedule of completion was <b>December 2024</b>.Update as per month wise Towers installation targets. Month wise Towers completion schedule is Feb- 24, Mar- 24, Apr- 112, May- 312, June - 189. 739 out of 1499 are done balance 760 towers to be tracked by July 2025.&nbsp; Out of balance 760 Towers, 115 sites having issues. The remaining 645 sites are distributed across the upcoming months. <b>April: 19 (achieved)</b>, May: 29, June: 55, July: 131, August: 241, September: 171. <b>Total 17 Towers installed in the month of May against target of 29. June USOF data to be provided by 07.07.2025 -</b></font>','2025-10-01 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,27,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.838986','2025-08-18 10:15:05.838986',NULL),(723,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">The state Govt. has been requested to <b>refund the number of foreclosed projects by<span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"> 30.04.2025</span> - A review meeting was held on 16.05.2025 with the State Government of Arunachal Pradesh. Detailed list of delayed (92) and foreclosure projects (6 full refund – NESIDS-OTRI &amp; 5 - As Is Where Is basis including 1 from SoNEC&amp; 4 from NESIDS – OTRI) shared with the State Government. Refund of fund to CFI already been initiated through implementing agency and it is under process.PWD processing refund to CFI.&nbsp; PWD has to deposit the Amount to BKN through AG office; all clearance has been done. –</b></font>','2025-08-21 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,28,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.843541','2025-08-18 10:15:05.843541',NULL),(724,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Promotion of organic farming with GI tagged products through support in branding and marketing. Steps to be taken to become the \"Orchid Capital of the World,\" capturing both domestic and international markets. - 7500 hectares converted under MOVCD-NER: branding and GI tagging initiatives in progress 20 products have been GI tagged and have received their GI Tag already completed. List of products have been received on 14.02.2025, and six of them are agricultural products. Next Update on 11/03 (done)</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,29,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.852365','2025-08-18 12:20:00.289093',4),(725,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Under National Mission on Edible Oils-Oil Palm (NMEO-OP), State to write to Department of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare (DAFW) for supply of quality saplings with a copy to MDoNER- Letter to DAFW sent; 8681 covered under plantation the supply of saplings has currently eased out there is no longer requirement to engage with Dept. Of Agriculture and FW. It can be closed. Done</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,30,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.857060','2025-08-18 10:15:05.857060',NULL),(726,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Govt. of Arunachal Pradesh was requested to send the brand ambassadors and local haat vendors from the state to Ashtalakshmi Mahotsav - Participation Successfully Completed; promotional materials dispatched</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,31,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.861474','2025-08-18 10:15:05.861474',NULL),(727,26,NULL,'<font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" size=\"2\"><u style=\"\"><b>Follow up on Action Items during <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Visit to Mizoram:</span></b></u></font>',NULL,1,'decimal',0,32,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.866569','2025-08-18 10:15:05.866569',NULL),(728,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Identification of priority sectorsfor development and saturation. State Government has selected Agriculture and Allied Sector as priority Sector for State.&nbsp; State will saturate Mizo Chili. SG will finalize the priority sector by 18.08.2025-</b></font>','2025-08-29 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,33,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.871545','2025-08-18 10:15:05.871545',NULL),(729,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Submission of proposal for construction of Heli-Concept at Thenzawl Mizoram</b>-In-principal approval has been recommended during EIMC meeting on 13.02.2025. State. DPR has already been uploaded on 30.04.2025. SG has been asked to share the Technical Feasibility Report for Heliport. SG uploaded the reply to NITI Aayog\'s observations on 4th July 2025 and has sought time till 28th July 2025 to submit the commercial feasibility report. <b>MoCA supported the proposal on 28.07.2025, subject to helipad design and specs conforming to DGCA CAR norms; Forwarded to State Government&nbsp;</b></font>','2025-08-25 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,34,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.876541','2025-08-18 10:15:05.876541',NULL),(730,26,NULL,'<div><font size=\"2\"><b>Submission of proposal on consolidated requirements for increasing <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Oil Palm production</span>.&nbsp;</b>SG made a detailed presentation on 07.05.2025. Below are the action points.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; i. Project to be developed on a cluster-wise basis, encouraging private sector participation.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; ii. Proposal to include a full value chain analysis from farmer to market, with branding and marketing strategies aimed at GI Tagging for Mizo palm oil.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iii. Low cost alternatives for CC road to be explored</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iv. Visit of Private player to be arranged with support from SG to understand the value chain</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; v. Present a comprehensive proposal with value chain analysis identifying role of SG, Line Ministry, Pvt Player and MDoNER</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">Revised presentation on <b>Oil Palm Production</b> held on 04.07.2025. Below are the action points. -<b>Instead of only road, SG will formulate a composite project on cluster facility.SG will submit revised presentation by 18.08.2025 - <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">19/08</span></b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; i. Assess industry size, current farmer beneficiaries, and potential downstream impact.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; ii. Clarify if the project supports existing stakeholders or expands to new ones.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iii. Map the ginger industry to identify scale and diversification potential.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iv. Review SHG organization; support formation and private linkages if needed.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; v. Explore setting up an integrated ginger processing centre.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; vi. Current capacity covers only 1.5% of state output; revise target to at least 50% for better value addition and market efficiency.</font></div>','2025-08-19 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,35,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.881233','2025-08-18 10:15:05.881233',NULL),(731,26,NULL,'<div><font size=\"2\">Submission of proposal for <b>Sports sector infrastructure development. – The concept note sent for</b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; i. <b>Construction of Multipurpose indoor hall,</b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\"><b>&nbsp; &nbsp; ii. Construction of Mizoram state sports council indoor stadium and</b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\"><b>&nbsp; &nbsp; iii. Establishment of multi-disciplinary sports infrastructure and uploaded on Purvottar Vikas Setu on 08.01.2025 under NESIDS-OTRI.</b> The Concept Note has been reviewed by NitiAyog and Sports MInistry, and the State Government of Mizoram is asked to provide additional details on equipment, coaching staff, training outcomes, the number of sports personnel, and site selection. <b>EIMC held on 29.04.2025.&nbsp; EIMC has recommended the concept note, Minutes have been issued on 19.05.2025.&nbsp; SG will submit the DPR by -&nbsp;</b></font></div>','2025-10-31 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,36,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.886092','2025-08-18 10:15:05.886092',NULL),(732,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Appointment of full-fledged Secretary of North-Eastern Council. - Appointed</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,37,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.890224','2025-08-18 10:15:05.890224',NULL),(733,26,NULL,'<div><font size=\"2\">State Government of Mizoram to provide duration analysis for approval of each of the new project proposals including the example analysis of the time taken on sanctioning of fund for the ongoing projects. - State has shared duration analysis of 3 delayed projects:</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; i. Fish farmer training center at Lengpui (SoNEC)- 11 Month delay- EIMC held on 13.01.25 in which project proposal was recommended by EIMC-(14 Cr.)- Done</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; ii. Construction of Thenzawl- Sialsuk via Sathlur and Lau River (Single Lane) (NESIDS-Road)- 7 Months delay. Recommended in EIMC Dt. 22.01.2025.&nbsp; AFS has been issued on 07.02.2025. (46 Cr.)- Done</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iii. Implementation of Educational infrastructure related to IT projects in 220 schools across Mizoram (NESIDS-OTRI)- 9 Months Delay*- DOT has supported the proposal with the provision of V-SAT. File has been approved by HMDoNER. Letter from HMDoNER to CM, Mizoram to be sent. 11/03 (done)</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; iv. Govt. of Mizoram was requested to send 40 local haat vendors from the state to Ashtalakshmi Mahotsav. - (Done)</font></div>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,38,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.894184','2025-08-18 10:15:05.894184',NULL),(734,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Follow up on Action Items during <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Visit to Arunachal Pradesh</span></b></font>',NULL,1,'decimal',0,39,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.898007','2025-08-18 10:15:05.898007',NULL),(735,26,NULL,'<div><font size=\"2\"><b>The <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">power sector</span> has been identified as a <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">priority sector</span></b>, with a detailed plan to be submitted. A proposal with an estimated cost of 13999.98 lakh for <b>illumination of 1224 un-electrified/partially electrified villages </b>and habitations with standalone solar home light and solar power plant at 255 public institutions is under preparation. <b>State Government made the presentation on on 04.07.2025. Below are the action points:</b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Electrify 12,000 rural households</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • 1 kW Solar PV with battery storage for homes &amp; community centers</font></div><div><font size=\"2\"><b>MNRE doesn’t do off-grid projects; MDoNER will fund from PM-DEVINe scheme. SG to submit the proposal after SLEC prioritization. State Government is unwilling to change the priority sector under PM Devine</b> –&nbsp;</font></div>','2025-08-19 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,40,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.903903','2025-08-18 10:15:05.903903',NULL),(736,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Submission of a proposal for revival and marketing of Tawang’s non-wood handmade paper </b>-Proposal Prepared and submitted to MDoNER for an amount of Rs 20 crore for consideration under the schemes of MDoNER. State Government will first set up a unit at an estimated cost of Rs. 4.95 cr. DPR has been uploaded on PVS portal and project considered in SEC meeting and <b>AFS has been issued on 21.07.2025. The Implementing Agency for Tawang’s non-wood handmade paper project is the Department of Textile and Handloom, Government of Arunachal Pradesh. The work has already been started. Tender has been floated on 04.08.2025. Progress to be monitored -&nbsp;</b></font>','2025-08-25 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,41,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.910041','2025-08-18 10:15:05.910041',NULL),(737,26,NULL,'<div><font size=\"2\"><b>Identification of <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">gaps in tourism sector</span> and support for viability gap funding from MDoNER/</b>other relevant Ministries.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <b>a. Presentation held on 04.07.2025. Below are the action points: Common Proforma sent to all 8 States after approval of Sec’y MDoNER on 11.07.2025</b></font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Propose 3–4-day itineraries.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Develop a full-cycle tourism plan (travel, stay, tours, cruises) under PPP with clear private sector roles.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Ensure end-to-end coordination from arrival to departure.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Include HR and capacity-building needs in planning.</font></div><div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp; &nbsp; • Highlight the project’s unique value proposition.</font></div>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',0,42,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.915280','2025-08-18 10:15:05.915280',NULL),(738,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Weekly timestamped and geotagged photos to be shared with the MDoNER- Mechanism Implemented for timely photo submissions- Submitted regularly. Implementing agencies have been informed- Done</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,43,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.920589','2025-08-18 10:15:05.920589',NULL),(739,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Promotion of organic farming with GI tagged products through support in branding and marketing. Steps to be taken to become the \"Orchid Capital of the World,\" capturing both domestic and international markets. - 7500 hectares converted under MOVCD-NER: branding and GI tagging initiatives in progress 20 products have been GI tagged and have received their GI Tag already completed. List of products have been received on 14.02.2025, and six of them are agricultural products. Next Update on 11/03 (done)</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,44,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.930819','2025-08-18 10:15:05.930819',NULL),(740,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\">Under National Mission on Edible Oils-Oil Palm (NMEO-OP), State to write to Department of Agriculture and Farmers Welfare (DAFW) for supply of quality saplings with a copy to MDoNER- Letter to DAFW sent; 8681 covered under plantation the supply of saplings has currently eased out there is no longer requirement to engage with Dept. Of Agriculture and FW. It can be closed. Done</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,45,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.939899','2025-08-18 10:15:05.939899',NULL),(741,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Follow up on Action Items during Visit to <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Nagaland.</span></b></font>',NULL,1,'decimal',0,46,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.944233','2025-08-18 10:15:05.944233',NULL),(742,26,741,'<span style=\"font-size: small;\">State Government has engaged&nbsp;</span><b style=\"font-size: small;\">EY</b><span style=\"font-size: small;\">, a third-party consultant on 13.05.2025 to do&nbsp;</span><b style=\"font-size: small;\">value chain analysis for handloom and handicraft sector&nbsp;</b><span style=\"font-size: small;\">and to come up with actionable points.&nbsp;</span><b style=\"font-size: small;\">And Completion of “Specialized Survey of Value Chain in Textile Sector” by –&nbsp;</b>','2025-08-15 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,1,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.949260','2025-08-18 10:15:05.949260',NULL),(743,26,741,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Appropriate action by State Government against the <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">five-point framework</span>. SG is prepared to present the State Action Plan to the Hon’ble Minister DoNER during Virtual meeting. Second State Review held on 22.07.2025. <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Minutes issued on 29.07.2025.</span>(done)</b></font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,2,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.953377','2025-08-18 10:15:05.953377',NULL),(744,26,741,'<font size=\"2\">Govt. of Nagaland was requested to send the brand ambassadors and local haat vendors for Ashtalakshmi Mahotsav-Action completed.</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,3,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.957522','2025-08-18 10:15:05.957522',NULL),(745,26,741,'<font size=\"2\">State government to do bottom-up analysis for Oil Palm cultivation- Analysis has been done by State Govt. and details shared with MDoNER.- (Done)</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,4,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.963212','2025-08-18 10:15:05.963212',NULL),(746,26,741,'<font size=\"2\">A nodal officer of the State to have regular coordination with MDoNER. Assistant development commissioner, Department of planning, Govt. of Nagaland has been Nominated as Nodal officers for MDoNER</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,5,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.967457','2025-08-18 10:15:05.967457',NULL),(747,26,741,'<font size=\"2\">State Government to work on sector specific recommendations (Education, Health, Transport and Connectivity, Economic Sector, Handicraft &amp; Handloom, Tourism, Organic farming, Agriculture &amp;Food processing (Egg, Fish and Milk)) made during the presentation- Nagaland Food Processing Policy has Notified on 17th March 2025 by 02/04. Done</font>',NULL,2,'lower-alpha',1,6,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.971606','2025-08-18 10:15:05.971606',NULL),(748,26,NULL,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Follow up on Action Items during Visit to <span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Tripura</span></b></font>',NULL,1,'decimal',0,47,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.975723','2025-08-18 10:15:05.975723',NULL),(749,26,748,'<font color=\"#000000\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, serif; font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\"><b>Telecom sector has been identified as priority sector.&nbsp;</b></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, serif; font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\">Phase-wise Plan/ PERT chart for Erection, Installation, Power connection and Commissioning of all 117 towers. As of January 27, 2025, 59 towers were commissioned. The remaining 60 towers are&nbsp;</font></font><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px;\">scheduled for completion by June 2025.&nbsp;</font><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px;\"><b>Total 86 towers out of 117 have been commissioned. Next update -</b></font>','2025-10-01 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,1,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.979830','2025-08-18 10:15:05.979830',NULL),(750,26,748,'<font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: rgb(249, 250, 251);\"><b style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">Kailashahar Airport:</b></font><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: transparent;\">&nbsp;MOCA&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, serif; font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: transparent;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\">to execute and Tripura Govt. to fund. A letter to MOCA with approval of HMDoNER has been sent on 31.01.25 for development of Kailashar Airport for 19-seater aircraft services. While agreeing for 19- seater aircraft operations, SG was also seeking financial support for ATR operations. Ministry wrote to SG asking them to proceed with 19-seater only for now. State to bear O &amp; M. Letter to CM has been issued on 18.06.2025.&nbsp;</font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, serif; font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: transparent;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\"><b>SG Tripura had written to AAI on 27.06.2025 requesting for expert evaluation of the project\'s O&amp;M cost. Meeting held between AAI, Tripura and Hon’ble Minister of Transport, Tripura. State Govt. to write to Chairman, AAI by 16.07.2025. AAI has sent O &amp; M cost to SG;&nbsp;</b></font></font><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: rgb(249, 250, 251);\"><b><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">File is under submission with CMO, Tripura; SG will convey their decision by 21.08.2025</span></b></font><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; text-indent: -24.189px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">-</font>','2025-08-21 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,2,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.984785','2025-08-18 10:15:05.984785',NULL),(751,26,748,'<p class=\"western\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; direction: ltr; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: Cambria, serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: medium; margin-left: 1.28cm; margin-right: -0.07cm; text-indent: -0.64cm; border: none; padding: 0cm;\"><font face=\"Arial, serif\" style=\"\"><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\">State Government to upload the status report w.r.t. </font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"><b>7 distressed projects</b></span></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\"><b> </b></span>along with supporting documents on Poorvatar Vikas Setu Portal for closure/ foreclosure of the projects </font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"background-color: transparent;\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\"><b>- </b></font></font><font color=\"#000000\" style=\"\"><font face=\"Arial Narrow, serif\" style=\"\"><b style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">4 projects completed, 1 dropped, 2 to finish by Aug, Oct, and Dec 2025 –</b></font></font></font></p>','2025-12-01 00:00:00.000000',2,'lower-alpha',0,3,'rich_text',NULL,'2025-08-18 10:15:05.989732','2025-08-18 10:15:05.989732',NULL),(752,26,748,'<font size=\"2\"><b>Upgradation of 19 Govt. ITI’s into center of excellence:</b> A comprehensive demand-side projection in consultation with industries &amp; a supply-side assessment of pass-outs from 19 ITIs for next 5 years will be done. State <b>has entered into partnership with TATA technologies Ltd. for comprehensive upgradation of all 19 Govt. ITI’s into center of excellence </b>- 02/06(done)<br><br><br><b>Setting up of ICD/CFS/AFS, extending VGF supports to PPP projects such as warehouses, logistics park, cold chain infrastructures; </b>and giving ‘white’ status to logistics industries. <b>The briefing note on ICD/CFS/AFS was shared with the state on 10.02.2025. The White Status will be included in the amended SLP. Presentation for Logistics Sector in NER was held on 21.04.2025. Letters have been sent on 06.06.2025 from Secy. MDoNER to CSs of States for action on pending issues. WIP compl